  "texts": [
    "This finding is consistent with Zhang et al.",
    "42 research, which points out that historical sites and cultural centers are crucial for shaping collective memory.",
    "However, some high-value points, such as Hexi CBD, exhibit extreme emotional polarization, suggesting that \"high frequency ≠ high recognition\", which requires further analysis of both positive and negative semantics in subsequent field interviews.",
    "The landmark element shows that natural mountains and city wall gates are scattered, forming a \"visual\" memory network.",
    "Comparing the historical timeline, pre-Ming Dynasty sites are frequently mentioned, while 20th-century industrial heritage appears only sporadically, revealing a gap in the current memory spectrum regarding modern history."
  ]
}